{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require child prices on tickets for concerts, events & holidays for under 16s",
        "additional_details": "I think some children over the age of 11 who are still in full-time education are unfairly excluded from receiving child pricing on tickets for events, holidays, and concerts.\r\n \r\nI think this can place an additional financial burden on families and alienate many teenagers who are eager to participate in these activities. I urge the government to require businesses and services to provide child pricing to all under the age of 16 who are in full-time education.",
        "background": "I want child prices on tickets for concerts or huge events and holidays to be exactly that. If you are under 16 and in education you are likely not earning a wage therefore I think should not have to pay adult prices for tickets.",
